prerequisites.description:
Add Match ExprKind variant to crates/reify-syntax/src/lib.rs:

```rust
/// Match expression: `match d { In => 1, Out => 2 }`
Match {
    discriminant: Box<Expr>,
    arms: Vec<MatchArm>,
},
```

Add MatchArm struct:
```rust
/// A match arm: `Pattern1 | Pattern2 => body`
pub struct MatchArm {
    pub patterns: Vec<String>,
    pub body: Expr,
    pub span: SourceSpan,
}
```

This is a type-only change.

Add CompiledExprKind::Match variant and CompiledMatchArm struct to crates/reify-types/src/expr.rs:

```rust
/// Match expression.
Match {
    discriminant: Box<CompiledExpr>,
    arms: Vec<CompiledMatchArm>,
},
```

```rust
/// A compiled match arm.
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct CompiledMatchArm {
    pub patterns: Vec<String>,
    pub body: CompiledExpr,
}
```

Also add a placeholder arm in compile_expr() in the compiler for ExprKind::Match to prevent compilation errors (emit diagnostic + return Undef), and a placeholder arm in eval_expr() in reify-expr (return Undef).
